{
  "page": "Benerro",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\"><img alt=\"Volantis.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e7/Volantis.svg/50px-Volantis.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e7/Volantis.svg/75px-Volantis.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e7/Volantis.svg/100px-Volantis.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> High Priest</span><br />Benerro</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/R%27hllor\" title=\"R&#39;hllor\"><img alt=\"Fiery Heart.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/67/Fiery_Heart.svg/50px-Fiery_Heart.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/67/Fiery_Heart.svg/75px-Fiery_Heart.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/67/Fiery_Heart.svg/100px-Fiery_Heart.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Mustamirri_Benerro.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Mustamirri Benerro.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/41/Mustamirri_Benerro.jpg/323px-Mustamirri_Benerro.jpg\" width=\"323\" height=\"560\" srcset=\"/images/4/41/Mustamirri_Benerro.jpg 1.5x\" /></a><div>Benerro by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://mustamirri.deviantart.com/\">mustamirri</a> ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Titles</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/High_Priest_(R%27hllor)\" title=\"High Priest (R&#39;hllor)\">High Priest</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Flame_of_Truth\" title=\"Flame of Truth\">Flame of Truth</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Light_of_Wisdom\" title=\"Light of Wisdom\">Light of Wisdom</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/First_Servant_of_the_Lord_of_Light\" title=\"First Servant of the Lord of Light\">First Servant of the Lord of Light</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Slave_of_R%27hllor\" title=\"Slave of R&#39;hllor\">Slave of R'hllor</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/R%27hllor\" title=\"R&#39;hllor\">R'hllor</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (appears)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Benerro</b> is the <a href=\"/index.php/High_Priest_(R%27hllor)\" title=\"High Priest (R&#39;hllor)\">High Priest</a> at the <a href=\"/index.php/Temple_of_the_Lord_of_Light\" title=\"Temple of the Lord of Light\">Temple of the Lord of Light</a> in the Free City of <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a>. His right hand is the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_priest\" title=\"Red priest\">red priest</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Moqorro\" title=\"Moqorro\">Moqorro</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Benerro&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Benerro\" title=\"Category:Images of Benerro\">Images of Benerro</a></div>\n<p>Benerro is a tall and thin man with a gaunt face and a lipless mouth. His skin is white as milk. Red flame <a href=\"/index.php/Tattoo\" title=\"Tattoo\">tattoos</a> cover his cheeks, chin, and shaven head. His high voice carries well.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/High_Priest_(R%27hllor)\" title=\"High Priest (R&#39;hllor)\">High Priest</a> preaches from a red stone pillar which connects to a lofty terrace of the <a href=\"/index.php/Temple_of_the_Lord_of_Light\" title=\"Temple of the Lord of Light\">Temple of the Lord of Light</a> by slender stone bridge.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Benerro can <a href=\"/index.php/Fire_magic\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fire magic\">make flames leap from his fingers</a>, and can trace fire in the air to form <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_glyphs\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Valyrian glyphs\">Valyrian glyphs</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> He also claims to be able to <a href=\"/index.php/Prophecy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Prophecy\">see the future</a> in his flames.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Moqorro\" title=\"Moqorro\">Moqorro</a> considers Benerro to be a <a href=\"/index.php/Slave_of_R%27hllor\" title=\"Slave of R&#39;hllor\">righteous slave</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The ruling <a href=\"/index.php/Triarch\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Triarch\">triarchs</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a> live in great fear of Benerro.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Benerro&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Benerro was bought by the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_temple\" title=\"Red temple\">red temple</a> while <a href=\"/index.php/Slavery\" title=\"Slavery\">enslaved</a> as a child.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Benerro&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Benerro&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>At the <a href=\"/index.php/Temple_of_the_Lord_of_Light\" title=\"Temple of the Lord of Light\">Temple of the Lord of Light</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a>, Benerro preaches that <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> is <a href=\"/index.php/Azor_Ahai\" title=\"Azor Ahai\">Azor Ahai</a> reborn, and he encourages many to support her. He says that Volantis will burn if the <a href=\"/index.php/Triarchs\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Triarchs\">triarchs</a> take up arms against Daenerys, and that they have \"turned away from the light\". Thousands of <a href=\"/index.php/Slave\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slave\">slaves</a> and freedmen crowd the temple plaza to hear Benerro preach every night.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Selhorys\" title=\"Selhorys\">Selhorys</a>, outside a <a href=\"/index.php/Red_temple\" title=\"Red temple\">red temple</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Haldon\" title=\"Haldon\">Haldon</a> overhear a <a href=\"/index.php/Red_priest\" title=\"Red priest\">red priest</a> relating Benerro's word of Daenerys to a throng of people, mostly <a href=\"/index.php/Slave\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slave\">slaves</a>. Haldon thinks they may be able to use Benerro's preachings to advance the cause of Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(Young_Griff)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (Young Griff)\">Aegon Targaryen</a>, and goes to find more information from <a href=\"/index.php/Qavo_Nogarys\" title=\"Qavo Nogarys\">Qavo Nogarys</a>. The customs officer tells them that Benerro's \"rantings\" have instigated fighting between the followers of <a href=\"/index.php/R%27hllor\" title=\"R&#39;hllor\">R'hllor</a> and those who worship other <a href=\"/index.php/Gods\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gods\">gods</a>. He says that Benerro and the other red priests should be quiet, or there will be retaliation.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Benerro's preaching unnerves the triarchs, because four out of every five inhabitants of Volantis are slaves, and they fear an uprising. However, the triarchs are powerless to stop him, because half of the city guard, the <a href=\"/index.php/Tiger_cloaks\" title=\"Tiger cloaks\">tiger cloaks</a>, worship R'hllor. Triarch <a href=\"/index.php/Malaquo\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Malaquo\">Malaquo</a> attempts to hire the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">Golden Company</a> to kill Benerro and purge the temple of his followers, but the <a href=\"/index.php/Sellswords\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellswords\">sellswords</a> refuse.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  \n</p><p>Not long after the arrival of Tyrion and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jorah_Mormont\" title=\"Jorah Mormont\">Jorah Mormont</a> in Volantis, they make their way to the <a href=\"/index.php/Long_Bridge\" title=\"Long Bridge\">Long Bridge</a>, and pass the red temple as Benerro is preaching. The crowd is packed solid, and they watch the priest address his followers. When Benerro's voice rises to a crescendo, Tyrion recognizes <i>Doom</i> and <i>Darkness</i> among the <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_glyphs\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Valyrian glyphs\">Valyrian glyphs</a> of flame which leap from his fingers. Benerro points at the <a href=\"/index.php/Black_Wall\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Black Wall\">Black Wall</a> and preaches that Daenerys is in danger, and he riles up the crowd. The mood of the crowd unnerves Tyrion, reminding him of the day of the <a href=\"/index.php/Riot_of_King%27s_Landing\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Riot of King&#39;s Landing\">riot of King's Landing</a>. He thinks it is a very bad idea for Aegon to try to ally with Benerro, and hopes that <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Jon Connington</a> has better sense than Haldon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Benerro secretly sends his right hand, <a href=\"/index.php/Moqorro\" title=\"Moqorro\">Moqorro</a>, as an emissary to Daenerys in <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Moqorro and soldiers of the <a href=\"/index.php/Fiery_Hand\" title=\"Fiery Hand\">Fiery Hand</a> travel on the ship <i><a href=\"/index.php/Selaesori_Qhoran\" title=\"Selaesori Qhoran\">Selaesori Qhoran</a></i>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> even though the ship's destination is <a href=\"/index.php/Qarth\" title=\"Qarth\">Qarth</a>, because Benerro sees in the flames that the ship will never reach that city.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The trading cog is eventually ruined by a storm in the <a href=\"/index.php/Gulf_of_Grief\" title=\"Gulf of Grief\">Gulf of Grief</a>, and Moqorro is lost overboard.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd40.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd40.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Moqorro is rescued from the sea by a <a href=\"/index.php/Longship\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Longship\">longship</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Victarion_Greyjoy\" title=\"Victarion Greyjoy\">Victarion Greyjoy</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Fleet\" title=\"Iron Fleet\">Iron Fleet</a> that is traveling to Meereen.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Benerro&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Benerro has sent forth the word from <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Her</a> coming is the fulfillment of an ancient <a href=\"/index.php/Prophecy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Prophecy\">prophecy</a>. From smoke and salt was she born to make the world anew. She is <a href=\"/index.php/Azor_Ahai\" title=\"Azor Ahai\">Azor Ahai</a> returned... and her triumph over darkness will bring a summer that will never end... death itself will bend its knee, and all those who die fighting in her cause shall be reborn...<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Haldon\" title=\"Haldon\">Haldon</a>, translating the words of a <a href=\"/index.php/Red_priest\" title=\"Red priest\">red priest</a> for <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Give me priests who are fat and corrupt and cynical, the sort who like to sit on soft satin cushions, nibble sweetmeats, and diddle little boys. It's the ones who believe in <a href=\"/index.php/Gods\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gods\">gods</a> who make the trouble.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Haldon\" title=\"Haldon\">Haldon</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Qavo</b>: Benerro's rantings will only serve to bring a savage wrath down upon his head.<br />\n</p><p><b>Tyrion</b>: What rantings?<br />\n</p>\n<b>Qavo</b>: In <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a>, thousands of <a href=\"/index.php/Slaves\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slaves\">slaves</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Freedmen\" title=\"Freedmen\">freedmen</a> crowd <a href=\"/index.php/Temple_of_the_Lord_of_Light\" title=\"Temple of the Lord of Light\">the temple</a> plaza every night to hear Benerro shriek of <a href=\"/index.php/Red_comet\" title=\"Red comet\">bleeding stars</a> and a <a href=\"/index.php/Lightbringer\" title=\"Lightbringer\">sword of fire</a> that will cleanse <a href=\"/index.php/Known_world\" title=\"Known world\">the world</a>. He has been preaching that Volantis will surely burn if the <a href=\"/index.php/Triarchs\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Triarchs\">triarchs</a> take up arms against <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">the silver queen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Qavo_Nogarys\" title=\"Qavo Nogarys\">Qavo Nogarys</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Flames had been <a href=\"/index.php/Tattoo\" title=\"Tattoo\">tattooed</a> across his cheeks and chin and shaven head to make a bright red mask that crackled about his eyes and coiled down and around his lipless mouth.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>When his voice rose in a crescendo, <a href=\"/index.php/Fire_magic\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fire magic\">flames leapt from his fingers</a> with a sudden <i>whoosh</i> and made the crowd gasp. The priest could trace fiery letters in the air as well. <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_glyphs\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Valyrian glyphs\">Valyrian glyphs</a>. Tyrion recognized perhaps two in ten; one was <i>Doom</i>, the other <i>Darkness</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Shouts erupted from the crowd. Women were weeping and men were shaking their fists. <i>I have a bad feeling about this.</i> The dwarf was reminded of the day <a href=\"/index.php/Myrcella_Baratheon\" title=\"Myrcella Baratheon\">Myrcella</a> sailed for <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Riot_of_King%27s_Landing\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Riot of King&#39;s Landing\">riot that boiled up</a> as they made their way back to the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Haldon_Halfmaester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Haldon Halfmaester\">Haldon Halfmaester</a> had spoken of using the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_priest\" title=\"Red priest\">red priest</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Young_Griff\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Young Griff\">Young Griff</a>'s advantage, Tyrion recalled. Now that he had seen and heard the man himself, that struck him as a very bad idea. He hoped that <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Griff</a> had better sense. <i>Some allies are more dangerous than enemies.</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Tyrion</b>: What is he saying?<br /> \n<b>Jorah</b>: That <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys</a> stands in peril. The dark eye has fallen upon her, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Triarchs\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Triarchs\">minions of night</a> are plotting her destruction, praying to their false <a href=\"/index.php/Gods\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gods\">gods</a> in temples of deceit... conspiring at betrayal with <a href=\"/index.php/Grazdan_mo_Eraz\" title=\"Grazdan mo Eraz\">godless outlanders</a>...<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Jorah_Mormont\" title=\"Jorah Mormont\">Jorah Mormont</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(Young_Griff)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (Young Griff)\">Aegon</a> will find no friend here. The <a href=\"/index.php/Red_priest\" title=\"Red priest\">red priest</a> spoke of ancient <a href=\"/index.php/Prophecy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Prophecy\">prophecy</a>, a prophecy that foretold the coming of a <a href=\"/index.php/Azor_Ahai\" title=\"Azor Ahai\">hero</a> to deliver the world from darkness. <i>One hero. Not two.</i> <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys</a> has <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a>, Aegon does not. The dwarf did not need to be a prophet himself to foresee how Benerro and his followers might react to a second <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Benerro can <a href=\"/index.php/Prophecy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Prophecy\">see the morrow</a> in his flames. <a href=\"/index.php/Triarch\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Triarch\">Triarch</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Malaquo\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Malaquo\">Malaquo</a> tried to hire the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">Golden Company</a>, did you know? He meant to clean out the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_temple\" title=\"Red temple\">red temple</a> and put Benerro to the sword. He dare not use <a href=\"/index.php/Tiger_cloaks\" title=\"Tiger cloaks\">tiger cloaks</a>. Half of them worship the <a href=\"/index.php/R%27hllor\" title=\"R&#39;hllor\">Lord of Light</a> as well. Oh, these are dire days in <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Old Volantis</a>, even for wrinkled old widows.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-15\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;The <a href=\"/index.php/Widow_of_the_waterfront\" title=\"Widow of the waterfront\">widow of the waterfront</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/R%27hllor\" title=\"R&#39;hllor\">Lord of Light</a>, bless your <a href=\"/index.php/Slave_of_R%27hllor\" title=\"Slave of R&#39;hllor\">slave</a> Moqorro, and light his way in the dark places of the world. And defend your righteous slave Benerro. Grant him courage. Grant him wisdom. Fill his heart with fire.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212